On 30 January 2025, a pro-EU protest was organized in Batumi City. Protesters demanded the release of political prisoners, including a journalist. They put up tents.
On 30 January 2025, protesters in Kutaisi City demanded the release of political prisoners.
On 30 January 2025, a rally to support a jailed journalist was organized in Kutaisi City.

On 30 January 2025, protesters in Tbilisi demanded release of political prisoners. Lelo organized a protest march from Marjanishvili metro station to Rustaveli avenue to support an arrested journalist. In the evening, protesters blocked traffic on Rustaveli avenue.

On 29 January 2025, a pro-EU protest was organized in Batumi City. Protesters demanded new elections and release of political prisoners. They tried to put up a tent, but police interfered and there was a skirmish, but ultimately the police allowed the tents to be set up.

On 29 January 2025, hundreds gathered in front of the Georgian Public Broadcaster in Tbilisi and demanded airtime for pro-EU protesters. Later they marched towards Rustaveli avenue and blocked traffic on the avenue.
On 29 January 2025, journalists staged a protest at the Mikheil Meskhi stadium in Tbilisi, alongside the visit of the prime minister, to support an arrested journalist.
On 29 January 2025, For Georgia organized a protest in front of City Hall in Tbilisi. The protesters accused the city hall of neglecting safety norms, which caused the death of a minor.
On 28 January 2025, a pro-EU rally was organized in Batumi City.

On 28 January 2025, journalists organized a protest to support an arrested colleague in front of the Special Investigations Service in Tbilisi. In the evening, pro-EU protesters blocked traffic on Rustaveli avenue and staged a performance to mark two months from the launch of the pro-EU protests.
On 27 January 2025, a pro-EU rally was organized in Batumi City. Meanwhile, journalists gathered at the prosecutor's office and demanded the release of an arrested journalist.
On 27 January 2025, a protest was organized in Gori City to support an activist, who had been kidnapped and beaten.

On 27 January 2025, pro-EU protesters blocked the traffic on Rustaveli avenue in Tbilisi. Students march to Rustaveli avenue from Tbilisi State University. Some protesters walked from the Georgian Public broadcaster. Meanwhile, protesters gathered at the prosecutor's office and demanded the release of an journalist. Later they marched to the Georgian Dream office.
On 26 January 2025, an activist in Gori City was kidnapped and beaten up by unidentified people in masks. He thought the incident was related to his participation in protests.
On 26 January 2025, a pro-EU protest was organized in Batumi City. Residents of Khulo also organized a protest at the university building.
On 26 January 2025, a pro-EU rally was organized in Kutaisi City. Protesters also gathered at the house of a judge who denied appeal to journalist.

On 26 January 2025, a protest march against police brutality was organized in Tbilisi from Didube metro station to the police building on Tsereteli avenue. In the evening, protesters blocked the traffic on Rustaveli avenue.
On 26 January 2025, a pro-EU protest was organized in Zugdidi City.
On 25 January 2025, hundreds of supporters of former president Mikheil Saakashvili, members of the United National Movement, demanded his release in Batumi City.

On 25 January 2025, students marched through Tbilisi streets and demanded the release of political prisoners. Several other marches were also organized from different locations towards Rustaveli avenue. In the evening, protesters blocked the traffic on Rustaveli avenue. Meanwhile students of Georgian National University protested outside campus.
On 25 January 2025, a protest was organized at the former Hippodrome in Tbilisi. Musicians organized a concert and rallied against construction in the Hippodrome.
On 24 January 2025, a protest march in support of political prisoners was organized in Batumi City.

On 24 January 2025, members of the For Georgia party organized a protest at the prosecutor's office in Batumi City and demanded that they release the full footage of a recent attack on the party leader of For Georgia.

On 24 January 2025, several protest marches were organized by the relatives and friends of the jailed protesters in Tbilisi. Protesters gathered at the office of the Georgian Charter of Journalism, metro stations Avlabari and Marjanishvili, as well as near the New Theatre and Tbilisi State University. Then they marched towards Rustaveli avenue.
On 24 January 2025, a protest was organized in Tbilisi at the City Hall to support public servants with critical opinions about the government.

On 23 January 2025, thousands gathered at a protest and performance organized by New Theatre crew in Tbilisi to support their jailed colleague, an actor. Following the performance, protesters marched towards Rustaveli avenue to join the daily pro-EU protest.
